reviews:
Really disappointed with the hotel after having read all the strong reviews and paid 550 euro per night. Booked the deluxe room - but received one looking into a wall, and balcony facing noicy AC fans making it un-usable. Size of room small (9-10m2 I would guess), but guess okay for paris.

SPA experience wasnt worth mentioning. Pool was not ‘spa warm’ at all, and rest felt crowded so we left directly again even though we had booked time.

Reception area and breakfast was nice and clean. Breakfast could probably defend the 4 star rating (not 5). Eg not possible to get anything else than a black coffee with milk.

Location is good and quite.

Our trip to Paris was to celebrate our 50th wedding anniversary. We wanted to stay somewhere special, and booked 11 nights at La Maison Favart. We definitely hit the jackpot with this booking. From the moment our car service arrived in front of the hotel, we were met with smiling, friendly faces. Things only got better from there. The lobby is beautiful, and hospitality abounds. Everything about this place is immaculate and tidy, in addition to being attractive and well decorated. Breakfast is available at an extra charge, and includes a variety of items to suit almost any preference. In the afternoon there is an honor bar available, as well as cake and coffee/tea. We had a fifth-floor room facing the plaza in front of the hotel. I will say the rooms are a bit small by American standards, although I do not believe it is unusual in a boutique hotel in Paris. We did not consider this to be a problem. The bed was comfortable, the room nicely decorated, and the bathroom was modern and spotless, with lovely toiletries and fluffy towels. No complaints whatsoever!
The view of the plaza proved to be an endless source of amusement for us. We watched small children playing soccer, mothers with baby carriages, and even a young couple doing the tango to boom box music! One day the plaza was complete occupied by a film crew, and we waved at the actors (they waved back!) and enthusiastically applauded their takes. The hotel is well located, with a Metro station just down the street. Restaurants abound within walking distance. Our compliments to every member of the staff at La Maison Favart. We love you all! If we ever are in Paris again, believe me, we will be back!

In one word, Fabulous.
This hotel was well situated, clean, trendily and offered the greatest concierge service compared to any high-end hotel I have experienced.
The room we stayed in was incredibly clean, the shower had the greatest water pressure and the bed was super comfortable.
This hotel also offered breakfast for a reasonable price with a reasonable offering; I wouldn’t pick this hotel for the breakfast but it was nice to have as an option on those mornings that were a little harder to get my legs in gear.

Beautiful hotel, well located for all the sights in Paris with most within a 25 minute walk.. we were upgraded to the suite on arrival (room 14) which was beautiful. Breakfast was lively and the ‘honesty’ approach to the bar was unique. Staff were genuinely lovely and couldn’t do enough to help.

My husband and I stayed at La Maison Favart for 6 nights in April .

Hotel is located in the heart of Paris with most sights and restaurants within a walking distance.
Louvre is only 15 mins walk away

We arrived early afternoon and our room was ready. The room was well appointed and hotel left us lovely wedding anniversary gift ( half bottle of champagne with their candle ) .

We used hotel spa twice during our stay and it was very good. It was a nice way to relax after full day of sightseeing.

We will definitely be back when in Paris.

Great experience; everything was perfect - the location, incredible level of hospitality, cleanness, decoration, and breakfast. The staff was very friendly and willing to help. I would definitely recommend the hotel.

Terrific staff and service. Excellent location. Enjoyable breakfast. Great amenities. Loved my room - very comfortable with a view of the Opera Comique. Freddy and Boris are excellent Concierges. I would recommend a stay at the Favart with no hesitation.

Never again. Key issue is there was construction going on next door for 2 weeks and due to go on for months and they didn’t tell us in advance. Their manager assured us when we booked ( the most expensive room in the hotel: La Petite Maison) that it would be quiet but it was far from it. Fireworks across the street at 1230am then woken by constant banging and hammering at 8am. Manager refused to accept that he should let customers know in advance of the construction next door and would only refund 2 of the 4 nights we booked for He even said that we were lucky he was giving us that since we booked a non refundable booking. Left after the 1 night and went back home to London. Worst trip in years.

Very sweet place in a superb location, walking distance to main attractions.
Welcoming staff! Cute and quet square just outside the hotel, a treasure in the busy city.
Recommend booking a room with a view on the theater.

This place is amazing. The staff are warm, friendly and extremely helpful. The room and location were beyond expectation. The metro plus many wonderful restaurants are located at the end of the street. Would recommend Le Maison Favart highly.

Amazing experience! Terrific staff and wonderful accommodations. The concierge service was top notch. The rooms were clean and charming. This was my first time in Paris and when I come back I would definitely stay at La Maison Faivart again.

Nice hotel. For me this is a 4 star hotel I guess. Not a strong 4 star hotel though. The location is great. The staff were very nice, helpful. They missed cleaning our room one day despite the early departure and sign on the door. I guess that can happen but shouldnt. The bathroom is ok. This was one reason why it is not a solid 4 star. The lobby bar is good to have but there was always only a tiny bit of wine left and no one could ever find a new bottle.

My friend and I really enjoyed our stay at Maison Favart! The staff was incredibly friendly and patient with me while I was practicing my French. It's a good location, and the rooms have really nice bathrooms with big showers and plenty of room.

La Maison Favart is my favorite hotel, ever! I have been staying there since 2016 and, each stay, it feels just as special to be there. It’s like a home away from home! The people who work there are so warm and kind, and they are a critical component of what makes this boutique hotel so unique and so wonderful. You would never regret staying at La Maison Favart! In fact, you will likely be so drawn in that you return again and again, with pleasure and delight!

This was our third visit to La Maison Favart and everything was still as wonderful as our last visit. The Concierge and Reception teams were so welcoming and helpful. The rest of the teams kept the hotel spotlessly clean and everything restocked. There was a good choice at breakfast and staff were on hand to help. The hotel location is close to a number of top attractions and lovely bars/restaurants. Can’t wait for our next visit!

This lovely hotel is exceptional! We spent 5 nights here, traveled for a few days and returned for 2 more nights so my review is based on an extended stay at La Maison Favart. Prior to our arrival, I had many helpful and pleasant email exchanges with the concierges, Freddy and Boris, who recommended restaurants, made dinner reservations and arranged transportation to and from the airport. This level of prompt, stellar service continued throughout our entire stay and was typical of all staff, who were also very kind and friendly. The hotel is located on a quiet street, but close to the metro and easy walking distance to major attractions, such as The Louvre, and fabulous restaurants. Our room was lovely and comfortable. Breakfast each day was delicious and plentiful with many options. Freddy and Boris could not have been more helpful; they guided us on the best means of getting to our destinations, suggested outstanding restaurants, recommended great things to see and do, and , frankly, were just overall wonderful. Upon our return to La Maison Favart for our last two nights in Paris, we were astonished to discover that we had been gifted by the hotel with an upgrade to an incredible suite and greeted with a bottle of complimentary champagne!! Wow! What an end to a fabulous stay at a marvelous boutique hotel! We will never stay anywhere else in Paris. We are so grateful to all the staff, especially Freddy and Boris, for all they did to make our visit to Paris so extraordinary!

Staff were very friendly and welcoming. They were helpful with finding places to eat and things to do. This place is a little out of the way and not much to look at from the outside. But it’s in a location that is about a 20 min walk from the Louvre and many things. Inside it’s cute and quaint. Rooms are small. Service excellent.

Excellent hotel! Great location! Lovely room, comfortable bed, nice in-room amentities. Very helpful staff at reception and guest services. Afternoon dessert with complimentary tea/coffee was very appreciated.

Fabulous time..beautiful hotel.great quiet location and Freddy and all the staff put the S in service. Boris really helped us when the SNCF site kept refusing our credit cards.

Highest praise for all

Three weeks for our honeymoon, never had we such a great concierge and hotel. The sauna, the massage room, the little daily surprise gifts, everything we asked was done immediately from reservations to taxis… it was the Royal treatment. Thank you Macicilia, Boris, Freddy, and all the others who went out of their way to make our honeymoon the most beautiful experience ever.

Amazing staff - just ask any one of them, and they will help you.
Great location - I guess it's near to train station. Bus rides. That was our first time in France and I'm bad in direction but didn't have a problem figuring things out. Explorers....
Thank you guys for upgrading our room also to a suite.... unexpected early gift, treat. Wow!
Enjoyed our stay and definitely would choose that location again on our next visit in France.

We stayed at La Maison Favart for two nights on our recent trip to France, which included a few days in Paris. The hotel was extremely accommodating-- from assisting us with airport to hotel transport, to upgrading our room to a beautiful suite to accommodate our travelers (family of three), to the phenomenal location near the Opera, it exceeded our expectations.

We highly recommend this hotel, and our next trip to Paris will certainly include a stay at La Maison Favart.

Fantastic boutique hotel. The staff was very professional and courteous. The room was clean and well appointed. We chose a suite to have a bit more room. Location was very convenient, just north of the Louvre Museum. Highly recommend.

Anamazinghotelwiththemostexcellentstaffwhohelpeduswithdinnerreservationsandvisitplans.ThelocationwasamazingwithacharmingviewoftheOperaComique.ShortwalktotheOperaGarnier,GaleriesLayfayetteforshoppingandwonderfulrestaurants.Everyoneofthestaffwasamazing-especiallyFreddie,Boris(concierges)andfrondeskMacicella.Breakfastwaseverythingweneededtoenergizeusforafulldayofsightseeing!!

Incredible service and location. The staff makes you feel like you are at home and has wonderful recommendations for what to do and where to eat in the city. Lots of great restaurants within very close walking distance. View of the opera was gorgeous and a source of entertainment each time we were in the room. Bed was comfortable and shower had excellent pressure!

Great location (approximately 40 mins taxi ride from CDG airport) within walking distance to very nice restaurants, cafe's, the Louvre and the Metro for everything else. The hotel is situated in quiet road in a safe and clean area which didn't cause us any disturbance at night or early morning. The gym and pool area is small but lovely and we had it to ourselves. The only thing I would say is that the family suite, although spacious enough, would probably not be suitable set up had our children been a bit older. The second bed is a shared sofa bed which was fine for a 14 and 12 year old but my older son would not want to have shared had he been with us. I would've preferred two single beds in that area which would be more suitable for families travelling with children a bit older. Overall, we loved Favart and would definitely come back. The staff make this place special. It felt very personal; a home from home with albeit more luxurious furniture!

From the moment we arrived we were made to feel at home and nothing was too much trouble. Allowed very early access to our room at no extra charge, all the staff were amazing and hotel was spotless. Easy to locate and one minute walk to the metro which made travelling in Paris very easy.

Another amazing stay at La Maison Favart. Each visit to Paris and this brilliant boutique hotel keeps getting better. Would not stay anywhere else in Paris. Aside from the beautifully decorated guest rooms & lobby and outstanding breakfast, the staff is wonderful and goes above and beyond to ensure your experience at La Maison Favarat is magnificient. The smooth check-in after a long overnight flight, restaurant recommendations for our family and friends and thoughtful birthday surprise for our teen son awaiting in our room after a full day sightseeing....everything was perfect. We love Paris and largely because of La Maison Favart. Thank you La Maison Favart. We are already looking forward to planning our next visit.

The whole stay at La Maison Favart was outstanding. The staff couldn't do enough and I will definitely be coming back. I must say a huge thank you to the reception desk staff for making everything so easy for us especially when my mum got sick. Merci x

We were there March 11 - March 18, 2023. All the Staff at La Maison Favart were very friendly and helpful, especially Macicilia and Freddy. They were our favorites. Everyone was very nice. They were always friendly, very helpful and most accommodating. The rooms were very clean, the hotel was very clean, the breakfast was great and they would always ask if they could help in any way. I shipped a box back to USA and they did everything for me. Freddy even called me to confirm info, etc. with the mailing/delivery process. They made sure we had someone to take us to the airport on the morning we left. (We left at 5 :15 a.m.) Always helpful in calling Taxi's, advising us on local sights to see and it goes on and on. Tom Mullally, my fiance cannot say enough great things about this hotel. It's also conveniently located. We will be going back to Paris at some point and we will definitely be staying there.
Kim Bodkin
Tom Mullally

This is the second time I have stayed at La Maison Favart with my chefs and culinary arts students. Each time we have stayed for a week and we did not want to leave. The hotel staff especially Carina, Maci, Freddie, and the evening concierge are so helpful and kind, they make you feel welcome and special. The hotel is spotless. The bathroom and shower are awesome. The bed is comfortable. Breakfast is perfect. The quiet street that the hotel is on is an oasis. I love this hotel.

This was our first time in Paris and I am so glad we stayed at Maison Faivart. It is a beautiful and luxurious boutique hotel. The concierge was so helpful, always offering recommendations and tips for shopping, dining and getting around. The hotel itself is beautiful, warm and inviting. The amenities offered make you feel at home. Some of the amenities I enjoyed was the heated towel bar, slippers, robes for the wellness area, turn in service every night, honesty bar and all day coffee and tea. Anything you may need is at your fingertips. The wellness area is such a luxury, and a an amazing amenity. The service was excellent, and we thoroughly enjoyed our stay. Maison Favart C’est magnifique!

Carina and her team go above and beyond to make you feel welcome and comfortable. I needed three items pressed and they had all items back to me in perfect order within hours. I left my electronic adaptor at home and they found me one to use. the breakfast is lovely and the cappuccino started my day off perfectly. We even had a family photo placed in our room along side a bottle of champaign. Just a lovely experience and hotel.

We stayed here for the first time , will not be our last . 30 mins walk from Gare de Nord, in fact this place is located very central to anywhere . The staff are top class , make you feel very much a friend , at home and a VIP, and it’s natural . From reception , concierge to the breakfast and room cleaning staff I must rate these guys the best , yes the best and I’ve stayed many places in cities , from London Savoy to Milan to many capitals including Rome Dorchester . I could write pages on how good this place is , but in summary I would highly recommend , and will be staying here every time I visit Paris . Thank you La Maison Favart 👍❤️

Perfect location and really friendly and helpful staff. Very close to Galeries Lafayette and there are super restaurants all around. Would definitely recommend and will definitely be returning to this great hotel.

I’ve just got back from a girls’ weekend, and we stayed at La Maison Favart. The hotel is beautiful and immaculately kept. The staff were brilliant, looked after us and ensured we had everything we need. They genuinely care about their guests. The ability to book spa slots was great and we enjoyed the pool and sauna.
The location was excellent, with ample choice of metro stations, cafes, restaurants and bars.
I don’t say this often but I really want to go back to the same hotel !

The location is super! Walk up to Sacre Ceur or down to Notre-Dame. Everything except the Eiffel Tower feels close by, but the metro easily solves that problem. The hotel staff have been wonderful. Thet always try to help you out with whatever problem or question you might have. The ability to book a time for the spa makes it so much more cozy and we used it every day with our two daughters who loved it. Breakfast is a good selection of quality ingredients without overdoing it and giving you unnecessary bad options just for the sake of having more options. They need to work on their internet connection when they have many guests, but hey, you are here for Paris, not Internet ; )

This trip was to celebrate our 50th anniversary and my wife’s 70th birthday so pressure was on to make sure everything was perfect. We have been to Paris about 10 times and we usually stay in the Latin Quarter. I wanted to have a more luxurious experience in a quieter and upscale area. I spent hours reading reviews and recommendations from sites like TripAdvisor and chose La Maison Favart to start and end our 16 day trip exploring Brittany, Normandy and Bruges in Belgium. This was one of the best travel decisions I ever made. They arranged for meet and greet at the airport (less than other private transfer services, the staff is warm and welcoming (saved me a lot of stress by storing a 28 inch suitcase till we got back to Paris), room overlooking courtyard is spacious and clean, my wife loved the pool/spa and finally I think the rates are reasonable. I highly recommend and this is be our “go to” place every time we come back to Paris.

We felt very comfortable in la Maison Favart : the room is tastefully decorated and we enjoyed the view of l'Opera-Comique every day. The staff was always friendly and helpful. We'll be happy to come back!

The hotel is spotless, and service is impeccable. Great location, lots of things in short walking distance but also feels peaceful. Freddy was super and helped with restaurant and bar recommendations, reservations and taxis when needed. Service was really warm and friendly but also professional and efficient. Our room was lovely, and serviced twice a day which was a pleasant surprise. We looked out over the Opera Comique and enjoyed seeing the comings and goings. There are lots of room options and a family suite too. Breakfast has many options and the spa was a nice addition - I tried out the massage bed and once I worked out what I was doing it was fab. Honesty bar was a good addition for a pre dinner drink. We’d love to return.

I had the pleasure of staying at La Maison Favart for my quick trip to Paris. The rooms were beautiful, comfortable, and quiet. Along with the location being outstanding. Freddie in particular was so helpful in helping us decide where to go and eat. Would 100% recommend.

This hotel was so quaint and fantastic! The rooms are very nice and clean and the staff are wonderfully helpful. The honesty bar is a real plus for those late night treats,. We walked form the train station to the hotel, and everything we wanted to see was either in walking distance, or close to a public transport stop.

We stayed here for 4 nights and everything was perfect. We were able to check in early even though check in isn’t actually until 3pm. Unfortunately the lift wasn’t working for the first few hours when we got there, however a very kind staff member carried all our luggage up the 5 flights of stairs with no problem at all. We had a beautiful room with a gorgeous view and enjoyed visiting the spa several times. Would definitely recommend staying here and will hopefully visit again☺️.

If you prefer a friendly, elegant boutique hotel instead of a busy, impersonal chain, this is the perfect pace to stay in Paris!

La Maison Favart is located between the 2nd and 9th arrondissement, a mere 15 min walk from the Louvre. It's on a quiet, picturesque square within 5 min of a major street and 10 min of major shopping centers.

The hotel itself is supremely comfortable and well appointed, with a nod to 18th century decor. The rooms are large by European standards, well appointed, and well maintained by an attentive housekeeping staff. Breakfast is fresh and varied, from bacon and eggs to cheese and croissants. The 'grotto' spa in the basement was an amazing surprise, including a small pool and sauna.

The best part of any hotel is the staff, and La Maison Favart boasts the best. From reception to the concierges, Freddy and Boris, everyone is warm, friendly, knowledgeable, and ready to help. That also includes the masseuse, who's an expert in deep tissue massage.

This hotel makes you feel welcome and comfortable 24/7 from arrival to departure. "Home away from home" is not an overstatement. I'll definitely return!

The staff was very friendly, polite and helpful! The room super nice and the location was perfect with many bars and restaurants near the hotel. Ask the reception to suggest restaurant for you. We had the best dinner after the receptionist booked a table for us and it was only 5 mins. to walk! Will definitely come back :)

Great hotel, it’s a pretty & clean boutique hotel with wonderful friendly staff. It was my daughters 21st & they made such an effort, I would definitely go back again. Also in a central location. The rooms were clean & they made a beautiful birthday display in the room for her arrival.

There’s a reason this hotel has so many great reviews from arrival to departure everything was perfect. The evening turning down service, amazing Paris retreat. I wouldn’t stay anywhere else!! Great location too.

Elegant small luxury boutique hotel in a fantastic location next to the beautiful Opera Comic. The staff are the best you can find. Very attentive, polite and friendly. The rooms are very clean and tastefully decorated. The shower is exhilarating. Best way to wake up and feel refreshed and energized for your morning. The honesty bar is a lovely gesture; they offer snacks and refreshments in the breakfast area from 3pm-11pm at no charge but also have alcoholic beverages available which can be used at your discretion hoping guests are honest to report their usage. We loved having tea or coffee with delicious coffee cake in the afternoon to unwind and relax after our explorations. The pool and dry Sauna are superb features, especially in Paris. The Hydro massage bed was very much needed to relax your tired body after long walks. Loved the massage bed. The location is fantastic. 5 minutes walking to Gallerie Lafayette and so many shops and restaurants. Paris is a walkable city and you can mainly walk to many attractions. The metro is just around the corner as well. Overall, this hotel is a fantastic choice in Paris. I loved our week long stay in this hotel and will definitely be back.

This hotel was gorgeous, and the service was wonderful. Freddy the concierge helped to make our visit truly unforgettable. Thank you Freddy! Your recommendations and restaurant reservations were fantastic, and loved that everything was walking distance from the hotel.

I had accidentally booked a non-refundable night (for the same night, and it was already 9 pm in Paris, while I'm in the SF Bay) instead of one 5 months hence, and was worried that the rather expensive room wouldn't be refunded, but Marwan, the front office manager, kindly refunded the total on request. So, while I didn't stay here, I will in the future!

I just wanted to reach out and express my appreciation for the wonderful stay I had at the hotel. The location was perfect, the room was super clean and beautiful, and the bathroom was spacious with great water pressure.
But what really made my experience special was the staff. Everyone was so friendly and helpful, but I wanted to give a special shoutout to Movair from the reception and Fready the concierge. They went above and beyond to ensure that my vacation was the best it could be.
I will definitely be back to stay at again in the future

Spent New Year’s in this hotel with family and couldn’t be happier with our decision. Staff were so helpful and accommodating. We look forward to returning soon.

The location was excellent and the rooms were cleaned everyday. Special mention to their concierge team who made sure we were well taken care of from airport pick up to drop off.

What a wonderful place! My 10 year old daughter and I had a fabulous 4 night stay here. Freddy and all the staff went the extra mile to make us feel welcome before and during our stay. The rooms are tasteful and clean and we loved the French boutique styling. The shower was excellent and our room was very quiet, with no outside noise to disturb us when the windows were closed. The air con/heating was silent and very effective too. The location was central and we were able to walk to all the sights. Excellent!

Absolute perfection!!! From the checkin to checkout the service, hotel, and experience was incredible! The concierge Freddy, was phenomenal! He is the best concierge I have ever had a hotel. He always made sure we had everything we needed, helped us book anything we needed including a last minute reservation at a restaurant on New Year’s Eve. The hotel was great as well! Nice and quiet and right next to a metro. Very easy to walk everywhere as well. We are so thankful for this incredible experience.

The best hotel experience, truly like a home. Everyone was extremely attentive and kind. The breakfast was enough to keep us going till lunch, lots of choices of proteins and cereals, breads and croissants. Our deluxe room with balcony was very nice, but next time I would skip the balcony request to get a view of the Opera, instead of a wall. Location is 5 star, everything is walkable, night or day! Book the spa with the pool, sauna and massage table - great after a long day of walking.

We stayed at here to celebrate the New year with the family. The hotel is very pretty and comfortable. The location is perfect for those who like to explore the centre of Paris. We will always remember the kindness of the staff and there efforts. They are the sweetest.

A pretty little boutique hotel in the perfect location. It’s beautiful, clean, with a warm and inviting atmosphere.

The decor and ambiance was so pleasant, I can’t overstate how ever single detail is on point.

My room was on the 6th floor , and nice a bed quite. The bed was comfortable and everything was super clean, with great amenities.

Staff where so friendly and helpfully too.

I especially loved the pool and sauna, I organised a private booking and had the whole place to myself, which was so relaxing and I felt nicely rejuvenating after a day out. It’s also picture perfect!

The Location was excellent, and in walking distance to where I wanted to be; close to all the major retail spots, and fashion store and close to the louvre.

I would most certainly revisit this little gem on my next visit to Paris

Good hotels are like friends. They generally are welcoming, hospitable and accommodating. However, just like friends you can set the great hotels apart from the good when something unexpectedly bad happens to you traveling and they rally around you like they are you family. I had just such an experience and cannot sing the praises of the Maison Favart staff loudly enough. From medical attention being called or simple accompanying me to the ATM because I was on crutches and vulnerable. Love this staff and they will tell you they are doing their “duty”. It is clearly more than that. Making guests safe and happy is their passion.

The hotel is at a great location. It is really clean and everything is well taken care of.
The staff is friendly and extremely helpful. I would recommend without any doubt. I will defenetly be going again in my next in city visit to Paris.

This hotel is the best value in Paris. Clean, great service and a central location. I will go there again anytime I am in Paris. They were very helpful when we needed to go for dinner and got us taxis. The Brefast is great.

We loved our stay at Hotel La Maison Favart so much. The best part was the breakfast in bed :). We could say what we wanted and when we wanted the breakfast a day before and the staff brought it to our room at the exact time we've said and it was perfect :). Also the location is perfect for a getaway in Paris. Would 100% recommend this hotel :)

The Hotel is so peaceful and elegant . Staff are so nice and will do anything for you . The underground pool is lovely and tranquil .
Great central position to get anywhere . Metro close by and plenty of Restaurants .

Great breakfast with plenty of choices .

We will be back next time we visit Paris 🇫🇷❤️

The staff was amazing and very accommodating. The concierges are of the highest quality and very skilled at making sure your stay is as pleasant as possible. There was a metro strike when I was there and taxis were very difficult to get that day, but the concierge was able to obtain me with a car service to and from the Palace of Versailles during the strike. I apologize for not remembering his name as I am terrible at remembering people's names. Also, the breakfast was quite lovely, I always enjoyed the chocolate-filled croissants, granola cereal, and yogurt with my coffee. The breakfast staff once again were very skilled, polite, and very attentive. The room was very nice as well. I felt it was more than enough space for me, with a very comfortable bed. There was a minibar that I didn't use, but the daily complimentary bottle of water was very much appreciated. The room was very clean. It was straightened up and cleaned daily. They also have a turn-down service in which a staff member would come by your room every evening in which they would replenish whatever you needed towels, soaps...etc. The hotel is also very conveniently situated for a tourist as most of the must-see tourist sites are within walking distance. Overall, my first trip to Paris was an outstanding, amazing, and joyous adventure thanks in no small part to them. Thanks for all the wonderful memories and I looked forward to returning in the future.

We had a very pleasant stay at La Maison Favart hotel. We were accommodated on the 4th floor, overlooking the beautiful building of the Opéra Comique. Our room was tastefully furnished, the bathroom were spacious and clean. The hotel's concierge, as well as the other staff, were courtly and accommodating. Unfortunately, we had to cut our stay short and checked out two days earlier, so we could not take advantage of the sauna, however we intend to visit the magnificent city of Paris some time soon and we'd love to stay at La Maison Favart again- this time for a longer period of time.

AMAZING hotel, staff and location. So many options for dinner within a five minute walk and metro lines that get you to sites all over the city in 5-20 minutes. There is absolutely nothing I can think to make it any better. I want to remodel my home to feel like our petit mansion. Impressive designs and every room is uniquely designed. Hotel is on a quiet opera courtyard off a busy street. We miss the staff they were so warm and friendly. We will absolutely visit again.

We stayed at La Maison Favart during our trip to Paris and all we can say: it was so so amazing. The staff was the kindest, the breakfast was delicious, the room was super nice and clean with a gorgeous french balcony with a view to the l’Opera Comique. The most important sights are within a walk distance, but the metro station is a 2 mins walk which makes life easier. If you’re looking for a cozy, elegant, romantic place, this is your place!!

I am convinced we have found the most wonderful hotel in Paris at LA Maison Favart. We went in early November and it did not disappoint. This impeccable boutique hotel is wonderfully situated overlooking the Comic Opera which was is beautiful and quintessential Paris. Everything about this hotel was exceptional, starting with the world class staff and concierge. Freddie and Boris at the concierge helped curate a wonderful and memorable experience. They were able to secure last minute reservations and tickets that we woudln't have been able to on our own. The concierge here is so delightful to work with and offers superb service that sets this hotel apart. The daily breakfast is excellent and a great value so make sure to add that to your booking. The hotel was exquisitely clean the whole time and offers turn down service so kudos to the housekeeping staff as well. The rooms are well appointed and had everything we needed. It was lovely to open the large shutters to let in fresh air. Another delight of this hotel is the spa which offers a sauna (although it wasn't working while we were there), a water massage table and small private pool. We highly recommend La Maison Favart and hope to be back.

We celebrated my mother's 80th birthday in Paris and had a very nice stay at La Maison Favart. The staff at the hotel are so nice and helpful and made us feel at home straight away. We chose La Maison Favart for the friendly staff, the good location near the Opera and great restaurants and because the hotel has an irresistibly cozy ambience. It was my and my wife's second stay and we will be more than happy to return.

Our two families stayed 5 nights at La Maison Favart in Paris, next to Opera Comique, walking distance to many sites in the center of Paris, such as Louvre or Place de la Concorde. The hotel is perfectly renovated and clean, all the staff including congierge and house keeping is very friendly. A few little things could be better: less lights in the room, just one mirror in the bathroom (not good when you are together in a room with two daughters ;), small tables for the breakfast, bad working WIFI in the upper floors. But besides that we loved the stay.

We were transitioning from a
Moroccan tour to a riverboat
adventure and needed a few
days to relax and unwind. This
hotel is perfect. The concierge
arranged for transportation from
the airport and then assisted us
during checkin...friendly and
efficiently. Our room (#24,) was
outstanding....comfortable,
spacious and quiet. Breakfast
offered many choices...all good.
The location allowed us to tour
and to easily find dinner spots
within walking distance. A great
lodging choice.

Lovely hotel, very original, wonderful, attentive service. great neighborhood. The Honor Bar is a great idea. I will return. Everything is really well decorated, comfortable. The room I had was not very large, but had everything I needed and was beautiful. The shower was spacious, which is almost more important than the size of the room!
Freddy, Boris and everyone were incredibly helpful and kind.

I visited La Maison Favart in 2017 and 2018 with family (see my prior review), and returned this month with my wife for a belated honeymoon. Despite a world pandemic since my last visit, it was just as lovely. The staff are all friendly and welcoming, the facility and rooms beautiful, the included breakfast is delicious, and the central location (near the Metro and major streets) makes it an easy launching point from which to explore the city. Staying at La Maison Favart has become a beloved tradition when I visit Paris, and now my wife and I look forward to returning there together!

Maison Favart is a great hotel with very nice and competent personnel. The breakfast is good and the rooms are pretty big and nicely laid out. We used a room targeted for wheel-chair use. Very effective and comfortable. When you swim jn the pool you can imagine any far away country around you; magic!

My husband and I spent five nights at this delightful, charming hotel. Each time we visit Paris, we stay in a different area. Maison Favart is in a great location with many places of interest within walking distance and convenient métro stops nearby.
What I loved best about this hotel- the minute you stepped in the door, you knew you were in Paris. The exquisite décor beautiful reflects this this marvelous city.
The hotel is meticulously clean and provides a very comfortable, spacious room. Our room even had a little balcony which was a plus.
To earn a good review, a hotel must have an excellent staff. We can’t say enough about the friendly, helpful staff, all of whom enhanced our stay.
The hotel offers an honor bar which we enjoyed as we took a drink up to our room after a busy day in the city. We are not breakfast people but decided to partake of breakfast before our long day of travel home. Not only was it delicious, but elegantly presented in their most pleasant dining space.
We had a lovely experience at Maison Favart and are pleased to pass along an enthusiastic recommendation.

Really the best Boutique hotel I found in Paris so far! Centrally located yet quiet, lovely decor in the public area as well as in the room, particularly liked the style of the bathtub and shower. The staff is very friendly and helpful! I will return.

Perfect for a single traveler. This small hotel became my home for almost two weeks. Everyone that worked here was so helpful and made me feel at home while I was in Paris. Boris, the concierge went above and beyond to make sure everything was taken care of for me. He even carried my box several blocks to the Post Office for me. The rooms were kept so clean, the little breakfast was sufficient and quaint. And the afternoon cakes were delicious. In a very good, safe location not far from Opera Garnier. Two Metro stops close by. I intend to stay here the next time I'm in town.

Another great, nice hotel that is centralized and near many cafés, shopping and restaurants. We were easily able to visit many attractions such as the Louvre, Centre Pompidou, Eiffel Tower and Arc de Triomphe. We were also within walking distance from metro stations which made it very easy to get around the city.

We spent 2 nights in this beautiful boutique hotel and we’re sorry it was such a short stay, but if we return to Paris for another visit La Maisonette Favart will be our 1st choice to stay.
Everything about the hotel was perfect, the helpful, friendly staff, the cleanliness, the facilities and the location. The staff even coped with my poor French!
The hotel is situated in a quiet square only a few metres from the bustle that is Paris, our room was on 5th floor and even with the window open there was no traffic noise.

Magical from the moment we walked in! The friendly front desk person showed us the Wellness Center, which includes a sauna, massage waterbed table, fitness room, and blue-lit tiny pool with waterfalls. Our room was a jewel box, with floor to ceiling windows overlooking the Comic Opera and small square. The room was super clean and comfortable. Breakfast was delicious, as were afternoon snacks. Just what we imagined in Paris!

I actually never write reviews but this hotel and its amazing team really deserves it. No matter for what reason you are travelling, is it for Business or leisure this Hotel is just perfect. Its super clean and the location is outstanding. All the Team is just super helpful and friendly, no matter if its the Backoffice, the Reception, the Concierge, the Cleaning and Kitchen Team. Thank you for always making our stay super smooth no matter if its with bigger groups for business purpose or with a small kid.

We just returned from 4 wonderful nights at La Maison Favart. It was our first time at the hotel and we were so happy we had chosen it. The central location was excellent and our room on the courtyard was charming, spacious and comfortable. The staff was friendly and super helpful. Freddy is the man!!! A concierge extraordinaire!
We so appreciated his help and suggestions!
We couldn't believe how pleasantly quiet it was, just steps away from the buzz of beautiful Paris. We will definitely be back!

This was by far our favorite place we stayed in Pairs. It is a beautiful hotel, top to bottom. The rooms are comfortable and quiet, the decor is gorgeous, and the location is excellent. We had many good meals within walking distance of the hotel and it was a great homebase for us to explore Paris. Additionally, I cannot say enough great things about Freddy. He the best hospitality professional that I have encountered. He was so helpful and went above and beyond to ensure that we had an excellent stay. I hope we can stay here again next time we are in Paris! Thank you Maison Favart!

We had a wonderful experience with La Maison Favart. First of all the location is excellent - 15 min. walk to Louvre, 10 min. walk to Opera Garnier and Galeries Lafayette, with great options of cafes and restaurants within minutes of walking distance. A Carrefour market is conveniently located about 5 min. walk away. The hotel itself is very clean, cozy and beautifully decorated. Although small, the room is equipped with everything we would need. The honest bar and swimming pool/sauna are great features providing some quiet moments and relaxation after a whole day of sightseeing.
The best part of the hotel is the professional and attentive staff. The booking team were very responsive answering my multiple questions during booking. We got a room (#47) with a view of Opera Comique adjacent to a quiet plaza, just as I asked for. During our stay, the front desk and concierge staff were never tired of helping us with various needs: restaurant recommendations & reservations, sightseeing information, transportations, etc. By the way, the restaurants Freddy and Monnier recommended were fantastic! I am sorry that I don't remember the name of each person, but I want to thank the whole team for making us feel home. It was our first trip to Paris and a truly amazing experience. La Maison Favart made it even more memorable. Merci Beaucoup!!

A great location, close to restaurants and shopping. Tucked in on a side street in a very safe part of Paris. The hotel looks great both inside and out, and the service is 5 star all the way. The staff was warm and friendly and were so patient with our very bad French! The concierge helped us with all our needs, including dinner reservations at two great (and walkable) French restaurants that were both were “booked up”. We have traveled quite a bit over the years and this place is as nice as any you will find. We will be back.

A beautiful boutique restaurant in 2nd Arrondissement. Staff were helpful and professional. Many tourist destinations were an easy walk within 20 minutes. Plenty of restaurants and shopping nearby. Very quiet location with view of Opera Comic.

We stayed in this hotel for one night, booked last minute due to a change in our flight schedule we arrived in Paris a day early!

The staff are extremely friendly, the location is good and the hotel itself is beautiful. Rooms are spacious (we stayed in an upgraded room) and very well designed.

We did not spend a lot of time here (you're here to see Paris after-all), but the hotel was a brilliant place to wind down, lay our heads and certainly added to our experience.

I have spent only 1 night in this fantastic hotel in the heart of Paris. I highly recommend this hotel if you are visiting Paris for short or longer stay. Don't forget to visit the Spa and ask the Concirge for tips on what to do around and where to eat.

This hotel was everything me and my best friend were looking for! It is very chic and so Paris! It’s so clean and decorated beautifully. Our room wasn’t huge but it was perfect for just us.

Has AC. Cleaned twice per day which was amazing. We did not get the included breakfast but around happy hour we did go down for free lemon cake and espresso.

The staff was so friendly and always willing to help out and make suggestions. When I return to Paris I will absolutely be staying here again and recommending to all my friends!

This was in a quiet area with a close walk to everything. Also easy to catch a cab a block away.

We have just returned from 5 wonderful nights in Paris. We found the hotel to be boutique, warm and welcoming. The staff are a real credit to the hotel.
Our room (Rm 51) was graded deluxe but was compact compared to others in the hotel. It did however have a great view of the comic opera and was well appointed. We particularly enjoyed having a mini fridge and coffee maker and access to fresh milk and pods/tea bags in the breakfast room (plus free cake!). As the floor space in the room is compromised by the main stairwell, we did find the shower room particularly small so perhaps ask for another room if space is an issue.
We really enjoyed using the hotel spa, in particular the water massage bed (what fun!). It’s bookable in advance so we always had the space to ourselves.
A good spread was laid out each morning for breakfast but we chose to eat out at a nearby bakery/cafe each morning. Do make use of the recommendations of the hotel concierges, we had a particularly wonderful cocktail on the rooftop of the cheval blanc hotel, thanks to Freddie.
We can also recommend the rooftop of the Galerie Lafayette for a fabulous view of Paris and the Astair restaurant in the nearby Colonnades.

I really do feel like Hotel Favart is like my Parisian home, I have been staying at this wonderful hotel for almost 40 years I love the romance, history and location of
La Maison Favart, and overlooking Opera Comique is magnificent. The staff are so wonderful and very helpful and especially Boris he is a gem. Thank you to everyone for making my stay just perfect. I so look forward to returning again and again. Your fabulous!

The Staff are friendly and very helpful, room was lovely and we would certainly stop at this Hotel again. Overall service was fabulous. Positioned within easy access to to the Metro it is a perfect base to explore Paris.

The room was great although it was on the ground floor next to the breakfast hall. The staff were very helpful. It's a small cosy hotel. The rooms are beautiful and clean and the location is pretty good as well. Would definitely recommend a stay there.

We were spending four nights in Paris and wanted to avoid staying in an impersonal hotel or chain. We happened upon La Maison Favart and boy are we glad we did. This is a small boutique hotel that delivers large. The staff were - to a person - helpful and cheery. The hotel itself is charming, located on a small side street in the heart of Paris. The hotel feels uniquely French in the best ways - the decor, the furnishings, the rooms. We had a lovely stay here. A few things of note:

- The rooms were large by Paris standards, especially the suite. Ask for a room overlooking the charming square directly outside the front door of the hotel, which overlooks a theater and often features locals dancing. Really.
- We didn't have the breakfast, but it looked lovely and robust. The complimentary coffee was delicious and a great way to start the day.
- The staff was all great, but a special shout out to Boris the concierge. He was amazing. We had a rather particular medical need during our stay for our daughter and he went out of his way to find us what we needed. He also had great recommendations, helped arrange for cars to/from activities, and was a gem of a help. Thank you Boris!

Just a wonderful place to spend time while in Paris. We'll be back!

Excellent staff very friendly and welcoming, standard room was good with excellent shower. Buffet breakfast with good choice for a boutique hotel, would definitely stay again if visiting Paris. Located 5 minutes walk from opera house with Metro close by.

A very beautiful and extremely clean hotel, with the most helpful and kind staff. The receptionist had a high level of professionalism, addressing our needs and making us feel at home. The service we received was outstanding in whatever we needed. We had such a pleasant and memorable stay!

Everything was excellent, starting with the room itself and ending with the human and service attitude of the local employees. Special thanks to Freddie, who was amazing and excellent and served us in the best possible way!

The room is a bit small, but not in a different way than is common in small hotels in Paris. The breakfast is very good (but it would have been more correct to take care of refilling all the things in the meal throughout the morning).

I cannot say enough good things about our recent stay at La Maison Favart. Every member of the staff was wonderful. We stayed in La Petite Maison, which I highly recommend for families of 4. We had plenty of space. Wifi was spotty in that room, but we had been advised that might be the case and the hotel had a mobile hotspot for us to use. That worked flawlessly.
The staff hurried to ready our room when we arrived very early in the morning after an overnight flight where we got no sleep. They offered us breakfast while we waited. They were eager to help out with any issue, including reservations and recommendations, help to use the metro, etc.
Carina, Boris, and every single member of the hotel staff was welcoming, helpful and friendly. We would return again in a heartbeat.

Cosy, clean and perfectly located hotel in the centre of Paris. The room was comfortable and clean. The pool is small but perfect for a quick swim after a warm day walking around Paris. The staff was very friendly and helpful throughout our stay. Would recommend it.

We were only at the hotel o e evening but it was lovely. The staff was great, we had a wonderful breakfast and the honour bar made it very easy to get a nice glass of wine when we wanted one !we would definitely stay again. My brother has 3 children and stayed in the petite Maison which was incredible.

This was our first stay at the La Maison Favart during our five nights Paris trip. The location was awesome and you could walk to everywhere. The rooms were beautiful and comfortable, and the staff was super friendly and couldn't do enough to help us (Thanks Nirou for the excellent service). There is small pool and sauna in the basement and it was refreshing.
The breakfast was more than adequate and offered scrambled eggs, various meats, lots of fresh pastries and coffee among other juices.
I highly recommend this hotel and we look forward to staying there again on our next trip to Paris
